<ul>
<li>Jain Saint</li>
<li>151 inch tall</li>
<li>Made from <strong>Ashtadhatu</strong> <strong>(octo-alloy) i.e. 8 metals</strong>, with Copper as major-&nbsp;gold, copper, silver, tin, zinc, iron, tin and antimony (or mercury)</li>
<li>In Pali, Rajasthan.</li>
<li>The metals are mixed in equal proportions to create the idol.</li>
<li>
<h2>Shri Vijay Vallabh Surishwer Ji Maharaj</h2></li>
<li>Jain saint</li>
<li>Disciple of Vijayanand Suri</li>
<li>Founder of Shri Parshwanath Jain Vidyalaya in Pali district of Rajasthan.</li>
<li>Estd Mahavir Jain Vidyalaya in Mumbai, Pune and Vadodara.</li>
<li>Supported non-violent movements of Gandhiji.</li>
<li>Estd institutions for girl childs, and brought women to the mainstream.</li></ul>